featured_reviews.review_id: Jama Masjid, Waidhan is a beautiful mosque which is located in the city centre. The masjid is the biggest mosque of the district and was built by the donations collected from the local muslims... The masjid has wonderful facilities for wudu, istinja and the hall where namaz has a capacity that more than 300 people can pray at at time.... also, if there are more people than the hall can adjust, the 2nd floor of the masjid is also present for praying. In conclusion, it is a beautiful place for ibadat...and the value of masjid is not its outside beauty but its inside beauty that there are always people present for ibadat....Subhan Allah.

featured_reviews.review_translated_text:
Jama Masjid Vaidhan, M.P. Singrauli district headquarters of the state is the grand mosque of Vaidhan and a very beautiful building which is the regional headquarters of Sunnah Wal Jamaat. In the construction of this luxurious mosque, Janab Haji Maulana Manzoor Ahmed Saida Sahab, Peshaimam and late Janab Mohd. Ayaz Khan Sahab of former Sadar Anjuman Committee were involved. It has played the biggest and special role. This is one of those special mosques in the world which has been built with the financial support of the local Muslim community. Apart from the Baidhan, the construction of the mosque without any external support or donation is worthy of pride.
At present, the arrangements are running smoothly under the supervision and instructions of our Sadar Mr. Shahnawaz Khan Sahib and Peshaimam Alijanab Haji Manzoor Ahmed Sahib.... Mujeeb Khan, Vaidhan
